The paper deals with language modeling, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also introduces a new neural network architecture, which involves handling long sequences and memory, making it relevant to machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper uses text datasets, which could also make it relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) if the text is being used for image captioning or other related tasks.
